{% extends "base.jinja" %}
{% block title %}Custom domain — {{ project.name }}{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
<section class="mx-auto max-w-2xl space-y-6">
  <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">
    <a href="{{ url('projects:dashboard') }}" class="font-medium text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300">← Projects</a>
    <span class="text-slate-600">·</span>
    <span class="text-slate-300">{{ project.name }}</span>
  </p>
  <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-6">
    <h1 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Custom domain</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">
      Default site URL: <code class="text-sky-300">{{ platform_fqdn }}</code>
      {% if student_public_port %}
        <span class="text-slate-500">(with port {{ student_public_port }} in local dev)</span>
      {% endif %}
    </p>

    <form method="post" class="mt-6 space-y-4">
      {{ csrf_input }}
      {% if form.non_field_errors() %}
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-rose-700/60 bg-rose-950/40 px-3 py-2 text-sm text-rose-100">
          {% for err in form.non_field_errors() %}{{ err }}{% endfor %}
        </div>
      {% endif %}
      <div>
        <label class="block text-sm font-medium text-slate-200" for="id_custom_hostname">{{ form.custom_hostname.label }}</label>
        {{ form.custom_hostname }}
        {% if form.custom_hostname.errors %}
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-rose-300">{{ form.custom_hostname.errors[0] }}</p>
        {% endif %}
        <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-slate-500">{{ form.custom_hostname.help_text }}</p>
      </div>
      <button type="submit" class="rounded-lg bg-sky-500 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-950 hover:bg-sky-400">Save domain</button>
    </form>

    {% if project.custom_hostname %}
      <div class="mt-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-700 bg-slate-950/50 p-4 text-sm text-slate-300">
        <p class="font-medium text-slate-200">Verification status</p>
        {% if domain_verified %}
          <p class="mt-2 text-emerald-300">Verified — traffic and TLS for this hostname are allowed once DNS (A/CNAME) points here.</p>
        {% else %}
          <p class="mt-2 text-amber-200/90">Pending — add the TXT record below, then click <strong>Check verification</strong> (or wait up to a few minutes for an automatic check).</p>
          <p class="mt-2 font-mono text-xs text-slate-400 break-all">TXT name (host): <span class="text-sky-300">{{ challenge_txt_fqdn }}</span></p>
          <p class="mt-1 font-mono text-xs text-slate-400 break-all">TXT value: <span class="text-sky-300">{{ challenge_token }}</span></p>
          <form method="post" action="{{ url('projects:domain_verify', slug=project.slug) }}" class="mt-3">
            {{ csrf_input }}
            <button type="submit" class="rounded-lg border border-slate-600 px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium text-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-800">
              Check verification
            </button>
          </form>
        {% endif %}
      </div>
    {% endif %}
  </div>

  <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/40 p-6 text-sm text-slate-300">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Cloudflare DNS</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">Point your domain at the same place as the platform app (Traefik / your server). Two common patterns:</p>
    <ol class="mt-3 list-decimal space-y-3 pl-5">
      <li>
        <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">CNAME (recommended for a subdomain like <code class="text-emerald-300">www</code>)</span><br />
        In Cloudflare → DNS → <strong>Add record</strong>: Type <strong>CNAME</strong>, Name <code class="text-slate-400">www</code> (or your subdomain label),
        Target <code class="text-sky-300">{{ platform_fqdn }}</code>, Proxy status <strong>DNS only</strong> (grey cloud) if TLS is terminated on your server,
        or proxied (orange) if you want Cloudflare in front (then align SSL mode with your origin).
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">A record (apex <code class="text-emerald-300">example.com</code>)</span><br />
        Type <strong>A</strong>, Name <code class="text-slate-400">@</code>, IPv4 address = your platform’s public IP.
        {% if public_ip %}
          Your server reports <code class="text-sky-300">{{ public_ip }}</code> in <code class="text-slate-500">PLATFORM_PUBLIC_IP</code> — use the real public IP Traefik listens on if different.
        {% else %}
          Set <code class="text-slate-500">PLATFORM_PUBLIC_IP</code> in the server environment so automated DNS helpers know the target IP.
        {% endif %}
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div class="rounded-2xl border border-emerald-900/40 bg-emerald-950/20 p-6 text-sm text-emerald-100/90">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-emerald-50">Allowed host &amp; CSRF</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      After you save a hostname, Django accepts that <code class="text-emerald-200">Host</code> header so you can see the “pending verification” page.
      Once the TXT check succeeds, the hostname is added to
      <code class="rounded bg-slate-950 px-1 text-emerald-200">CSRF_TRUSTED_ORIGINS</code> as well, and Traefik gets a route for that host.
      You do <strong>not</strong> need SSH or env edits for each student domain.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-400">
      You still configure the <strong>A record</strong> in Cloudflare (pointing at your server IP). Traefik must route that hostname to this app; after saving, run
      <code class="text-slate-300">regenerate_traefik_routes</code> on deploy (or use the prod compose startup command).
    </p>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-400">
      If you run <strong>several web workers or servers</strong>, use a shared cache (Redis) for <code class="text-slate-400">CACHES</code> so every worker learns new hostnames quickly; otherwise each worker picks them up on first request or after a short cache TTL.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
{% endblock %}
